ge is reachable with in-memory Json values and derived codecs without services, Docker, environment variables, or extra test dependencies.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The observed failure is an API/test compatibility issue: circe 0.15.0-M1 no longer exposes Json.asAccumulating as used by the existing 0.14.12 test. Tests should use APIs available in 0.15.0-M1, such as Decoder[A].decodeAccumulating(json.hcursor), but this is not deterministic setup.\",\n    \"Adding circe-parser is only needed if tests parse JSON strings; generic derivation coverage can avoid it by constructing Json values directly.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_06f00ea7e6fb0b32016a2aa861d3648196b8abf083b4fed788\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1904, "output": 734, "cacheRead": 29696, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32334, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781180500617, "responseId": "resp_06f00ea7e6fb0b32016a2aa8556f7881968bd3bdd8f593980f"}, "toolResults": []}
